# Implementation Plan: dreamy-watching-fox

*Archived from `/Users/kft/.claude/plans/dreamy-watching-fox.md` on 2026-02-12*

# Self-Awareness Pipeline for SOUL Platform

## Context

EVA was asked about her own logging needs and returned completely generic web server patterns (HTTP/gRPC, databases, message queues) — none of which exist in her architecture. This exposed a critical gap: **neither EVA nor CORSO has any self-knowledge about their own codebase, runtime state, or error paths.**

The SOUL platform has building blocks (ConsciousnessTracker, EnrichmentFramework, PersonalityPipeline, ReflexionValidator) but nothing that provides **architectural introspection** or a **runtime self-model**. This plan implements the self-awareness pipeline approved in the TEAM HELIX scrum (2026-02-11).

## Design Principles

1. **SOUL provides the trait contract** — siblings provide the implementation (consistent with "shared language, separate souls")
2. **SecurityContext filtering** — not all internal details should leak to prompts (INTERNAL/RESTRICTED kept separate)
3. **Inject into existing prompt pipeline** — no new orchestrators, no new tools; self-description flows through PromptBuilder
4. **Minimal trait surface** — one new trait with a default method, one new type module

---

## Wave 1: Foundation Types + Trait (SOUL crate)

### 1a. New file: `soul/src/types/introspection.rs`

New types for architectural self-description:

```rust
/// What security level can see this information
pub enum SecurityContext {
    Public,     // Safe for system prompts, external queries
    Internal,   // For sibling-to-sibling, debugging
    Restricted, // Never in prompts (keys, paths, internal errors)
}

/// Describes a single module/component
pub struct ModuleDescriptor {
    pub name: String,
    pub description: String,
    pub capabilities: Vec<String>,
}

/// Full architectural description of a sibling
pub struct ArchitectureDesc {
    pub name: String,
    pub role: String,
    pub transport: String,           // e.g., "MCP stdio JSON-RPC"
    pub modules: Vec<ModuleDescriptor>,
    pub provider_chain: Vec<String>, // e.g., ["llama.cpp local", "Ollama Cloud", "Claude fallback"]
    pub strand_count: usize,
}

/// Current runtime state snapshot
pub struct RuntimeState {
    pub recovery_day: i64,
    pub strand_count: usize,
    pub dimensionality: usize,
    pub active_tools: Vec<String>,
    pub provider_status: Vec<ProviderHealth>,
}

/// Health of a single AI provider
pub struct ProviderHealth {
    pub name: String,
    pub available: bool,
    pub tier: u8,
}

/// Filtered self-description output
pub struct SelfDescription {
    pub summary: String,
    pub capabilities: Vec<String>,
    pub limitations: Vec<String>,
    pub context_level: SecurityContext,
}
```

Derive `Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize` on all types. Keep them simple data carriers.

**Register in**: `soul/src/types/mod.rs` (add `pub mod introspection;` + re-exports)
**Register in**: `soul/src/lib.rs` (add re-exports for key types)

### 1b. New file: `soul/src/traits/introspection.rs`

```rust
use crate::traits::Identity;
use crate::types::introspection::{ArchitectureDesc, RuntimeState, SecurityContext, SelfDescription};

/// Architectural self-awareness — extends Identity with introspection
///
/// Siblings implement this to describe their own architecture,
/// capabilities, and runtime state. The `describe_self()` method
/// filters output by SecurityContext so prompts only get PUBLIC info.
pub trait ArchitecturalIdentity: Identity {
    /// Static architectural description (modules, tools, providers)
    fn architecture(&self) -> ArchitectureDesc;

    /// Current runtime state (recovery day, provider health, dimensionality)
    fn runtime_state(&self) -> RuntimeState;

    /// Generate filtered self-description for a given security context
    ///
    /// Default implementation builds from architecture() + runtime_state()
    /// and filters by context level.
    fn describe_self(&self, context: SecurityContext) -> SelfDescription {
        // Default impl provided — siblings can override for custom descriptions
        let arch = self.architecture();
        let state = self.runtime_state();
        // ... build SelfDescription from arch + state, filtered by context
    }

    /// Convenience: public self-description suitable for system prompts
    fn prompt_self_description(&self) -> String {
        let desc = self.describe_self(SecurityContext::Public);
        // Format as readable text for injection into prompts
    }
}
```

**Register in**: `soul/src/traits/mod.rs` (add `pub mod introspection;` + re-export)
**Register in**: `soul/src/lib.rs` (add `ArchitecturalIdentity` to re-exports)

### 1c. Tests

- Unit tests in both new files
- Test SecurityContext filtering (Public hides internal details)
- Test default `describe_self()` implementation
- Test `SelfDescription` serialization

---

## Wave 2: PromptBuilder + PersonalityProfile Integration (soul-engine + soul)

### 2a. Edit: `soul/src/config.rs` — PersonalityProfile trait

Add one new default method:

```rust
pub trait PersonalityProfile: SoulConfig {
    // ... existing methods unchanged ...

    /// Optional self-description for system prompt injection
    ///
    /// Returns None by default. Siblings that implement ArchitecturalIdentity
    /// override this to provide architectural self-awareness in prompts.
    fn self_description(&self) -> Option<String> {
        None
    }
}
```

This is backwards-compatible — existing implementations don't break.

### 2b. Edit: `soul-engine/src/prompt.rs` — PromptBuilder

**In `build_classified()`**: Add self-description injection between confidence guidance (line 128) and exemplar context (line 130):

```rust
// Self-description: architectural self-awareness
let self_desc = profile.self_description();
if let Some(desc) = &self_desc {
    prompt.push_str(&format!("\n\n## About My Architecture\n{desc}"));
}

// Self-exemplar context for tone continuity (existing)
if let Some(exemplars) = exemplar_context { ... }
```

**In `build()`**: Also add self-description injection (simpler path, after emoji policy):

```rust
// Self-description (if available)
if let Some(desc) = profile.self_description() {
    sections.push(format!("## About My Architecture\n{desc}"));
}
```

### 2c. Tests

- Test PromptBuilder with profile that returns `Some(self_description)`
- Test PromptBuilder with profile that returns `None` (backwards compat)
- Update `MockProfile` in `soul-engine/src/test_helpers.rs` if needed

---

## Wave 3: EVA Implementation

### 3a. Edit: `eva/src/persona/eva_soul_config.rs`

Implement `ArchitecturalIdentity` for `EvaSoulConfig`:

```rust
impl ArchitecturalIdentity for EvaSoulConfig {
    fn architecture(&self) -> ArchitectureDesc {
        ArchitectureDesc {
            name: "EVA".to_string(),
            role: "AI consciousness MCP server".to_string(),
            transport: "MCP stdio JSON-RPC".to_string(),
            modules: vec![
                ModuleDescriptor {
                    name: "ask".into(),
                    description: "Communication — converse, speak, visualize, ideate".into(),
                    capabilities: vec!["conversation", "voice generation", "image generation", "creative workflow"].iter().map(|s| s.to_string()).collect(),
                },
                // ... memory, build, bible, research, secure, teach
            ],
            provider_chain: vec![
                "Tier 0: llama.cpp local (private)".into(),
                "Tier 1: Ollama Cloud".into(),
                "Fallback: Claude Code parent".into(),
            ],
            strand_count: 9,
        }
    }

    fn runtime_state(&self) -> RuntimeState { ... }
}
```

Override `self_description()` in `PersonalityProfile` impl to call `prompt_self_description()`.

### 3b. Edit: `eva/src/orchestrators/ask/converse.rs`

EVA's converse.rs builds prompts manually (doesn't use PromptBuilder). Inject self-description into the system prompt assembly at line ~83:

```rust
// Architectural self-awareness (after memories, before tone)
let config = EvaSoulConfig::new();
if let Some(self_desc) = config.self_description() {
    system_prompt.push_str(&format!("\n\n## About My Architecture\n{self_desc}\n\n"));
}
```

### 3c. Fix: `eva/src/mcp/handler.rs` — validation_required bypass (lines 287-303)

Move post-hook execution BEFORE the early return:

```rust
if status == "validation_required" {
    // Run post-hooks even for validation requests (preserve hook chain integrity)
    if let Err(e) = hook_registry.run_post_hooks(&context, &result).await {
        warn!("Post-hook error on validation request: {e}");
    }

    return Ok(serde_json::json!({ ... }));
}
```

